# Mobile ↔ Backend Integration

## HTTP methods must match backend routes

`fetch(url)` defaults to **GET**. Check `backend/app/main.py` and `docs/realtime-protocol.md` before calling any API.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — causes HTTP 405 if route is POST
await fetch(`${baseUrl}/v1/auth/dev-token?user_id=demo-user`);

// ✅ GOOD
await fetch(`${baseUrl}/v1/auth/dev-token?user_id=demo-user`, { method: "POST" });
```

Prefer `src/services/backendApi.ts` for backend REST calls instead of inline `fetch`.

## Never use localhost on physical devices

```typescript
// ❌ BAD on real iPhone
"http://localhost:8000"

// ✅ GOOD — use resolveBackendUrls() from src/config.ts
`http://${macLanIp}:8000`
```

Do not default `app.config.ts` `extra` to localhost; use `EXPO_PUBLIC_*` env vars or runtime IP from `Constants`.

## Expo SDK must match Expo Go

Before changing `expo` in `package.json`, confirm Supported SDK in Expo Go (Settings). Align project SDK; document changes in `docs/troubleshooting.md`.

## Smoke test after mobile/network changes

1. Fetch Dev Token → `token ready`
2. Connect → `session ready`
3. Send Text → agent reply
